","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"basic level"}]},{"text":" has two characteristics that can be set for system, subsystem, or category (in the Console app we can mute every single one of them, even the process, even filter by type like error -> you can even save one filter that you create ):","type":"text"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Enabled (does it actually produce a log?)","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"isItStoredToDisk","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" or Memory (memory: memory buffer, saved to disk only on fault or error)"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Levels are hierarchical, therefore by setting Debug to go to disk, implies that Info (and Default) will also go to disk","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Default behavior:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"WWDC16-721-behavior","type":"image"}]},{"level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Privacy","text":"Privacy"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Prevent accidental logging of Personally Identifiable Information (PII)"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Dynamic strings, collections, arrays, etc. are assumed to be private"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"WWDC16-721-privacy","type":"image"}]},{"level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Architecture","text":"Architecture"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"WWDC16-721-architecture"}]},{"level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Faults-and-Errors","text":"Faults and Errors"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Faults and Error log information are captured into a separate set of log files"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"